title: Black hat and red ribbon
description:
[b]Black hat and red ribbon [/b]

What inspires an artist? A photograph by an Italian photographer found in a collection of old books. A woman that entices the mind and the heart. A black hat with a red ribbon.

Together they add up to a lovely painting that exudes an aura of youth, playfulness and romanticism.

The Albanian born painter Gazmend Freitag, who lives and works in Linz, Austria, is known for his colorful erotic paintings and his lovely portraits in pencil and pastels. Here he uses strong brushstrokes, complementary colors and a wonderful play of light to define the rather ethereal appearance of a young woman, who seems to try on the black hat as a source of strength and confidence. The casually held towel mirrors the red of the ribbon and serves as a counterweight.

title: Portrait of Ursula Roschger
description:
The first time I saw you

The first encounter, the first glance… we all know that special moment, when everything seems possible and the world is a wonderful place. Gazmend Freitag catches the magic and expectations of such a moment on canvas. Radiant Green and Red communicate a sense of immediate aliveness. The focus of the painting – the young woman- is bathed in light and appears to be glowing from within. To give expression to his feelings, the artist has put himself into the frame as an adoring observer, who tenderly reaches for his dream.

title: The green stockings

title: Ginger and Fred 5
description:
HOMAGE TO GINGER AND FRED BY GAZMEND FREITAG
 
This graphic work, drawn by Gazmend Freitag in 2014 for a group exhibition at the prestigious Roman E. Svabek Dancing School in Vienna, pays tribute to Fred Astaire, “Master of the Dance Floor” and one of the most famous dancers in film history, and Ginger Rogers, his dream partner on the silver screen and in tap dancing. In “Homage to Ginger and Fred”, Gazmend Freitag captures the glamour of this dance couple and also the feeling from the Golden Age of Hollywood in the 1930s and 1940s.
 
Gazmend Freitag, an artist whose artistic work is always centered on the human figure and portraits, has focused in his realistic ink and pencil drawing on the interplay between the dancing couple and on the rhythm and ease of their swinging motion. In this picture he emphasizes typical features and characteristics to reproduce the aura and magic especially evident in tap dancing.

title: THE OLD RAILWAY BRIDGE IN LINZ
description:
A PICTURE FOR THE AGES – THE OLD RAILWAY BRIDGE IN LINZ!

Gazmend Freitag, the well-known Albanian international painter and Kosovo native, has lived and worked in Linz for a number of years. “Bridges” are a subject that has always fascinated him, occupying an important place in his creative work.

Linz’s Nibelung Bridge, the historic Ottoman stone arch bridge built in his hometown of Prizren in the 15th century, the Scalzi Bridge in Venice, the Aire de Loisirs de Pons in France – all of these structures have already appeared in Gazmend Freitag’s art.
 
“There’s something in a bridge that strikes a chord in me,” said Freitag. “Any bridge to be torn down leaves a void that can never again be filled.“
 
Now his “Bridge Cycle” has been augmented by yet another meaningful work.
 
An important concern for the artist is to preserve in canvas the 116-year-old historical railway bridge in Linz for posterity as it is going to be soon dismantled due to its poor condition and replaced with a new structure. The first sketches were finished by Gazmend Freitag in February of this year, shortly before the bridge was closed. Now the main work, an enormous oil painting of the old “Iron Lady”, has just been completed and titled the “Linz Railway Bridge”.

title: THE NIBELUNGEN BRIDGE IN LINZ
description:
THE NIBELUNGEN BRIDGE IN LINZ 

There is a bridge that links the past to the future. At one end where the bridge runs between houses and ends in an open space on the main square, there used to stand a post marking the zonal border between two of the powers that once occupied Austria and had shared the bridge. But even after they withdrew their forces, the bridge and its mighty pillars remained. They thrust themselves before the viewer’s eyes as they push away of the blue of the river, oscillating between light and dark and at some points even merging into a shimmering white, all of which makes the picture appear friendly. The milky light blue sky likewise lightens the composition Gazmend Freitag has created. However, the picture is centered on the gray-white railing curving to connect one bank of the river to the other. Welcoming the bridge to the other side is the bright green hue of trees covering the front of the gray building to the right of the picture. The building’s muted grays and browns and the pillars of the bridge merge together in Gazmend Freitag’s painting with the milky blue sky and the vigorously flowing Blue Danube into a harmonious whole. The bright white street lights hovering above the railings dynamically outline and underscore the curved lines of the arched bridge railings.

title: Eagle
description: In mythology, the eagle is linked with the sun. Its power, strength and radiance moreover make it the world's most important emblem, after the lion. Majestic, proud and mighty; it circles in the sky. The eagle not only rules the air, but is also a very special animal. This symbolism is also expressed in the work of Gazmend Freitag.

title: Expectation
description:
[b]“Expectation” — Gazmend Freitag and the eroticism of the female body[/b]

Voluptuous sensuality, vibrant colors and an all-promising white dominate this painting by the Albanian artist Gazmend Freitag, who is known for his erotic drawings and portraits. Painted in the tradition of the European Impressionists it shows his love for detail, strong colors and the eroticism of the female body.

Sittings for commissioned works like this one take place in the sunny studio of the artist in Linz. Clients as well as models appreciate the calm and professional manner of the native Albanian, whose passion for beauty is at display in all of his work. (MG)

title: Stonebridge in Prizren
description:
The beautiful bridge of Prizren with the montains all around. The light in this picture give it a special atmosphere. 

Gazmend Freitags relationship with Kosovo and the town where he was born is deeply emotional and also an expression of pride in the history of the Albanian nation and the beauty of Albanian nature. That is why he has also immortalized on canvas the Old Stone Bridge (Ura e Gurit), a neighborhood in Prizren with characteristic craft shops and scenic surroundings. 
 
Notwithstanding that he was born on May 25, 1968 in Pataqan i Poshtëm, a community in the Rahovec district of Prizren, since leaving in 1990 he has spent more than half of his life in Germany and Austria and his longing for his hometown and his country connects him emotionally to all that is beautiful and good therein. Private collection!

title: Apples and Cider
description:
An invitation to sit down and to enjoy the bounty of autumn. Crisp red apples, cider in a green mug and the golden light playing on the wall create a serene and relaxing atmosphere that any guest will enjoy.

Painted in the tradition of the Old Masters, the canvas shows the skill of the artist in the layering of color and in the play of shadow and light.

title: Sonjuschka’s Dance
description: Gazmend Freitag sees his colleague artist Sonjuschka as the subjective embodiment of the modern feminine ideal of beauty: her shoulder-length blonde hair, charming and with much heart and soul.  Again and again, Freitag finds the inspiration to create works that stir him, testifying to the feeling and skill, of which he has demonstrated plenty.  His colleague’s passion for dance has been captured by Gazmend Freitag in his very own special, quite sensitive style. Sonjuschka’s Dance is at once a compliment on her beauty and the essence all women express in general.

title: The Kiss
description:
Joe Leitner, Betreiber der ersten Kunstraum-Fanpage auf Facebook hat im Juni 2013 die erste VAKO-Ausstellung im Kunstraum organisiert. Nach seinem Konzept der variablen Kommunikation (VAKO) führte der Kurator Facebook-Künstler-Freunde aus dem virtuellen Raum in den realen Kunstraum, in Der Kunstraum in der Ringstrassen Galerien Wien vonHubert Thunhofer. Ich war auch Teilnehmer der Ausstellung mit 4 Werken in Öl.
 
Hier lernte ich Joe Leitner auch real kennen und seine Frau Traudi auch. Hier passierte der Kuss von den beiden genau vorm einem Bild von mir (Nu avec livre). Ich war begeistert über die zwei Liebenden, die alles um sich herum vergessen hatten, da sie sich innig tief küssten. Es war ganz klar dass ich davon ein Bild malen werde, da ich sehr inspiriert war.
 
Der Kuss im Kunstraum, Öl auf Leinwand, 100 x 80 cm gemalt im Jahr 2013 ist bis jetzt ausgestellt worden: 
 
Künstlerische VHS Wien, im Rahmen der KUNST BRAUCHT ÖFFENTLICHKEIT, KUNST FÜR ALLE Ausstellung 2013.
 
Im Rahmen des Frühlingsfestes 2015 von Art of Hair-Fashion-Lifestyl-Beauty, Art, Fotografieartista Keti Berisha im Seed Design, Wien, für zwei Wochen.

title: Baresha
description:
[b]Oil portrait of an Albanian Baresha who is not as traditional as it seems.[/b]
 
Colorful portrait of an Albanian shepherdess. She looks more like an Albanian princess than a shepherdess. I want to show that the most important thing in life is not what kind of work you do, but how happy it makes you. This picture has been selected for the 1st  Biennale of Creativity in Verona in February 2014.
